- Re-add critique mode when ready for production. What it was: (1) Actor prompt — LLM suggests 3–5 candidate next steps (each a one-liner), returns JSON with `candidates[]` and `objections[]`. (2) Critic prompt — same conversation + list of candidate actions, LLM scores each 0–100 for probability of closing, returns JSON `evaluations[]`. (3) Backend: pick highest-scoring candidate as `advice`, send coaching payload including `candidates` (so FE can show alternatives). (4) Frontend: optional toggle "Critique" (e.g. in Coach panel); when on, send `critique_mode: true` in WS init and `set_critique_mode` when toggled; SessionView showed "Critique #N" and list of candidate actions when `tip.candidates` was present. Removed for latency (two LLM calls) and product simplicity. To re-add: restore ACTOR_CANDIDATES_PROMPT and CRITIC_PROMPT in app.py, implement get_coaching_with_critique(conversation, objections, …) calling actor then critic, branch in do_coaching/process_commands on critique_mode, add critiqueMode state + Critique checkbox + onCritiqueChange in App.tsx and SessionView, and handle `candidates` in useCoachWs + TipCard.
